        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "67414cc74b8aa57e285d083cab87577a10fd0a1f",
            "subject": "LU-1512 oi: reuse idle OI blocks"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-09-11 07:07:30.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Lai Siyao",
          "email": "lai.siyao@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-08-28 07:37:51.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-1881 oi: not shrink the last entry in OI index node",
        "message": "LU-1881 oi: not shrink the last entry in OI index node\n\nShrinking OI index node to recycle idle leaf for the last entry\nwill cause subsequent lookup/insert ops to access invaild space.\nSo just keep the last entry there, which can be reused directly\nby next new node.\n\nOther fixes:\n\n1) The recycled empty OI blocks should be recorded on divice and\nbe re-loaded after the device remounted. Then they can be reused\nwhen needs new OI blocks.\n\n2) Need not check iam_container::ic_idle_failed in iam_new_node().\n\n3) Clear iam_frame::at_shifted when iam_path_release().\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <yong.fan@whamcloud.com>\nSigned-off-by: Bob Glossman <bob.glossman@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I55403f329ec5c0dfe7faeb054418edf83ee82e38\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
  },
